<div class="header">Addendum</div>
On the first of June, 2025, one significant incident had been reported involving a group of unsuspecting wanderers.
The wanderers, whose full names have been excluded upon request from their families, were seeking refuge in the level, requesting advice from the various PAPs, when one of them, Penelope, had unknowingly aggravated a PAP after uttering about how "pissed scared these egotistical mannequins are" within its vicinity. Subsequently, the PAP had seemingly gathered a group of around a dozen PAPs to start attacking Penelope. The other wanderers who were present at the scene had ran while shouting for help, bringing it to the attention of other wanderers, who subsequently got teleported to levels they reported to be highly unstable in terms of mental effects.

Shortly after the incident, [[Backrooms Investigation Foundation|B.I.F.]] members had begun installing preventative measures to ensure the maximum separation of wanderers and PAPs as possible. A change in level class is currently pending.

<blockquote>"I know how tempting it is to go here, especially considering the low risk class and the "new color", but it's really not worth it. It may be safe as long as you do not communicate nor interact with any of them, but you and I both know that's just not going to happen. These so-called "Proud American Patriots" are more technologically advanced than us, yet appear to be less easy-going and more defensive of preserving their ideal world. Just take my word for this,  ''everything'' in the backrooms should be approached as if it's too good to be true, even if it isn't."</blockquote>

One important thing to note is a seemingly invisible force that the PAPs identify as a "threat", it is possible that they have installed security measures of sorts to kick out wanderers. Many PAPs discuss about a potential war, and they may just be invisible to us, just like they once were before the discovery of <span style="color:#64ffda;">olo</span>.


<div class="header">Recovered Logs</div>

'''4/24/2025 - "Two wanderers rediscovering Level 912"'''

 [Gabriel and Ismail claim to have been sitting under a tree at the time, presumably in [[Level 231|Level 231's Park]]]

 Gabriel: Yo, uhm, Ismail? Do you remember that one neighborhood we saw that nobody back at [[M.E.G.]] believed us about?

 Ismail: Yeah, no wonder why we left those glorified criminals.

 Gabriel: Well... do you remember it too? Like, in vivid detail? The unique choices of colors, fashion, just about everything.

 Ismail: Huh... strange. I do? I remember something about—people there.

 Gabriel: I knew it. We have to go spread the word.

 Ismail: Don't you think it's a little unsafe for just us two to go there? We don't know what could be lurking.

 Gabriel: You're right, Ismail, we have got to bring Penelope with us!

 Ismail: [sigh] Sometimes I wonder why I even decided to live with you.

 [end]



'''6/1/2025 - "Interview with Penelope"'''

 B.I.F. Agent: Penelope, what do you last remember about the incident in Level 912?

 Penelope: Well. Uhm.

 Agent: Take your time, Penelope.

 Penelope: I didn't think they'd hear me. I'm sorry.

 Agent: All is forgiven, but what exactly happened?

 Penelope: I was just walking and I was- ganged up on, and then I vanished to [[Level 610]].

 Agent: Mhm. What happened there?

 Penelope: The walls just- were shifting and then I saw a bright opening leading to this other [[Level 511|level that kept shifting]].

 Agent: I see. Where did you end up next?

 Penelope: [[Level 9]], before I was escorted here.

 Agent: What else do you remember seeing in Level 912?

 Penelope: Well- those PAP things, they're severely anxious, they don't like anything even mildly threatening towards them. I could've sworn I saw multiple of these weird military installations, probably much more advanced than whatever we have. The propaganda posters everywhere depict increasingly violent acts. The red starts to fade into-

 Agent: Thank you and good bye, Penelope. We hope to see you soon.

 [end]



<div style="font-size:35px;font-family:Optima;background: linear-gradient(360deg, rgba(0,0,0,0.24), rgba(12, 23, 26,0.01));margin:0.5em; padding:10px;border-radius:120px 80px 25px 25px"><span style="color:#64ffda;">Entrances</span></div>
Entering a turquoise (mysteriously not painted <span style="color:#64ffda;">olo</span> as well) house in [[Level 85]] near a mailbox with the words "American Dream" written on it will take you directly to one of Level 912's houses.

Asking people for directions in [[Level 594]], following their advice, and then somehow getting lost will take one here.

[[Level 434|Lever 434]] may lead here through yet another turquoise house.

[[Level 231]] can lead here just from the mere memory of Level 912.

The entrances are anywhere familiar enough.

<div style="font-size:35px;font-family:Optima;background: linear-gradient(360deg, rgba(0,0,0,0.24), rgba(12, 23, 26,0.01));margin:0.5em; padding:10px;border-radius:120px 80px 25px 25px"><span style="color:#64ffda;">Exits</span></div>
Mentioning any sensitive topics relating to beliefs deemed "threatening" to PAPs and subsequently getting arrested by local law enforcement will send one to [[Level 245]].

Unlocking the basement door of any of the houses will take you to [[Level 918]], though this doesn't apply to the PAPs.

Realizing something negative about, or in the level while residing in the level will immediately send you to [[Level 610]] or [[Level 913]], amongst other unidentified levels in which wanderers had begun exhibiting negative thoughts.

Anywhere but here.

